        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 4:46PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 446 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Variadero to 6 miles northeast of
Pastura, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Santa Rosa, Santa Rosa Lake State Park, Cuervo, Puerto De Luna,
Variadero, Conchas Lake State Park, Conchas, Conchas Dam and
Trementina.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 257 and 299.
State Road 104 between Mile Markers 44 and 81.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
